				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Coming back to the bard<a name="15521"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 13 04 11:47 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>There's a big difference between FV and Zek servers and the rest of EQ. On most servers, high-end tradeable items are pointless except for twinking or for reselling to people who are twinking- by the time you can afford them, you can also get equally nice (or better) nodrop items via nearly risk-free camps, quests, or LDoN merchants. 
<br />

<br />
That's not true on the special servers; on FV, you can buy most anything but you can only have as many twinks as you have spare accounts, so big investments tend to go to the main character which makes the economy rather odd. On the Zeks, there's a whole list of reasons why camps and quests are more risky. (not to mention the high population of certain classes, including bards, increases competition for those classes' drops)</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%">"All that is gold does not glitter,
not all those who wander are lost;
The old that is strong does not wither,
deep roots are not reached by the frost.
From the ashes a fire shall be woken,
a light from the shadows shall spring;
Renewed shall be bla</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
